-- Persian Gulf Stocks: Emaar Economic City and Khaleeji Commercial
-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 2012-05-02T12:54:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-02/persian-gulf-stocks-emaar-economic-city-and-khaleeji-commercial.html
The  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  decreased for a
sixth day in the longest losing streak since November, declining
1.6 percent at the 2 p.m. close in the emirate. Saudi Arabia’s
 Tadawul All Share Index (SASEIDX)  was little changed.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Emaar Economic City (EMAAR)  , a unit of the developer of
the world’s tallest tower, rose 1.1 percent to 13.35 riyals.
Emaar Middle East started handing buyers keys to homes in Saudi
Arabia’s eastern province.  Khaleeji Commercial Bank (KHCB)   fell for the first time
since April 10, losing 2.4 percent to 0.04 dinar. The Bahraini
lender said it gave Dubai’s Meydan a $40 million loan.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
